2062
02:21:11,586 --> 02:21:13,629
What is your motto here?

2063
02:21:13,713 --> 02:21:17,800
Boys, inform on your classmates,
save your hide,

2064
02:21:17,884 --> 02:21:21,262
anything short of that,
we're gonna burn you at the stake?

2065
02:21:21,346 --> 02:21:23,514
Well, gentlemen,

2066
02:21:23,598 --> 02:21:26,976
when the shit hits the fan,
some guys run,

2067
02:21:27,060 --> 02:21:28,686
and some guys stay.

2068
02:21:28,770 --> 02:21:32,231
Here's Charlie, facin' the fire,
and there's George,

2069
02:21:32,315 --> 02:21:34,817
hidin' in big daddy's pocket.

2070
02:21:34,901 --> 02:21:36,527
And what are you doin'?

2071
02:21:36,611 --> 02:21:40,573
You're gonna reward George
and destroy Charlie.

2072
02:21:42,325 --> 02:21:43,826
Are you finished, Mr. Slade?

2073
02:21:43,910 --> 02:21:46,037
No, I'm just gettin' warmed up.

2074
02:21:47,080 --> 02:21:49,123
I don't know who went to this place.

2075
02:21:49,207 --> 02:21:52,210
William Howard Taft,
William Jennings Bryan,

2076
02:21:52,293 --> 02:21:53,878
William Tell, whoever.

2077
02:21:53,961 --> 02:21:57,256
Their spirit is dead,
if they ever had one.

2078
02:21:57,340 --> 02:21:58,674
It's gone.

2079
02:21:58,758 --> 02:22:01,636
You're buildin' a rat ship here,

2080
02:22:01,719 --> 02:22:04,639
a vessel for seagoin' snitches.

2081
02:22:04,722 --> 02:22:08,476
And if you think you're preparin'
these minnows for manhood,

2082
02:22:08,559 --> 02:22:10,103
you better think again,

2083
02:22:10,186 --> 02:22:15,942
because I say you are killin' the very spirit
this institution proclaims it instills.

2084
02:22:17,193 --> 02:22:18,778
What a sham.

2085
02:22:18,903 --> 02:22:21,823
What kind of a show are you guys
puttin' on here today?

2086
02:22:21,906 --> 02:22:25,368
The only class in this act
is sittin' next to me.

2087
02:22:25,451 --> 02:22:29,163
And I'm here to tell you
this boy's soul is intact.

2088
02:22:29,247 --> 02:22:31,999
It's non-negotiable.
You know how I know?

2089
02:22:32,083 --> 02:22:35,753
Someone here, and I won't say who,
offered to buy it.

2090
02:22:36,170 --> 02:22:38,214
Only Charlie here wasn't sellin'.

2091
02:22:38,297 --> 02:22:39,715
Sir, you're out of order.

2092
02:22:39,799 --> 02:22:42,051
I'd show you out of order.

2093
02:22:42,135 --> 02:22:45,138
You don't know what
out of order is, Mr. Trask.

2094
02:22:45,221 --> 02:22:47,390
I'd show you, but I'm too old,

2095
02:22:47,473 --> 02:22:49,976
I'm too tired,
I'm too fuckin' blind.

2096
02:22:50,059 --> 02:22:55,481
If I were the man I was five years ago,
I'd take a flamethrower to this place!

2097
02:22:58,609 --> 02:23:01,738
Out of order?
Who the hell you think you're talkin' to?

2098
02:23:03,322 --> 02:23:05,491
I've been around, you know?

2099
02:23:06,159 --> 02:23:08,327
There was a time I could see.

2100
02:23:08,828 --> 02:23:10,413
And I have seen.

2101
02:23:10,997 --> 02:23:13,291
Boys like these,
younger than these,

2102
02:23:13,374 --> 02:23:16,711
their arms torn out,
their legs ripped off.

2103
02:23:17,295 --> 02:23:22,258
But there is nothin' like the sight
of an amputated spirit.

2104
02:23:22,341 --> 02:23:25,219
There is no prosthetic for that.

2105
02:23:26,971 --> 02:23:30,433
You think you're merely sendin'
this splendid foot soldier

2106
02:23:30,516 --> 02:23:33,728
back home to Oregon
with his tail between his legs,

2107
02:23:33,811 --> 02:23:37,732
but I say
you are executin' his soul!

2108
02:23:39,025 --> 02:23:40,359
And why?

2109
02:23:41,277 --> 02:23:43,654
Because he's not a Baird man.

2110
02:23:44,322 --> 02:23:47,158
Baird men.
You hurt this boy,

2111
02:23:47,241 --> 02:23:50,036
you're gonna be Baird bums,
the lot of you.

2112
02:23:50,203 --> 02:23:52,455
And, Harry, Jimmy,

2113
02:23:53,289 --> 02:23:55,958
Trent,
wherever you are out there,

2114
02:23:56,042 --> 02:23:57,627
fuck you too!

2115
02:24:00,213 --> 02:24:02,131
Stand down, Mr. Slade!

2116
02:24:02,215 --> 02:24:03,716
I'm not finished.

2117
02:24:04,884 --> 02:24:09,138
As I came in here,
I heard those words,

2118
02:24:09,222 --> 02:24:11,182
cradle of leadership.

2119
02:24:12,391 --> 02:24:17,813
Well, when the bough breaks,
the cradle will fall, and it has fallen here.

2120
02:24:17,897 --> 02:24:19,482
It has fallen.

2121
02:24:19,565 --> 02:24:22,568
Makers of men,
creators of leaders.

2122
02:24:22,693 --> 02:24:26,072
Be careful what kind of leaders
you're producin' here.

2123
02:24:27,031 --> 02:24:31,160
I don't know if Charlie's silence
here today is right or wrong.

2124
02:24:31,244 --> 02:24:32,745
I'm not a judge or jury.

2125
02:24:32,828 --> 02:24:34,622
But I can tell you this,

2126
02:24:34,705 --> 02:24:38,459
he won't sell anybody out
to buy his future!

2127
02:24:39,752 --> 02:24:42,922
And that, my friends,
is called integrity.

2128
02:24:43,881 --> 02:24:45,758
That's called courage.

2129
02:24:45,883 --> 02:24:49,053
Now that's the stuff
leaders should be made of.

2130
02:24:54,600 --> 02:24:58,104
Now I have come to
the crossroads in my life.

2131
02:24:59,272 --> 02:25:02,608
I always knew
what the right path was.

2132
02:25:03,609 --> 02:25:06,946
Without exception, I knew,
but I never took it.

2133
02:25:07,446 --> 02:25:08,948
You know why?

2134
02:25:09,574 --> 02:25:12,535
It was too damn hard.

2135
02:25:14,161 --> 02:25:17,248
Now here's Charlie.
He's come to the crossroads.

2136
02:25:17,331 --> 02:25:20,793
He has chosen a path.
It's the right path.

2137
02:25:21,794 --> 02:25:25,464
It's a path made of principle
that leads to character.

2138
02:25:28,467 --> 02:25:30,887
Let him continue on his journey.

2139
02:25:32,972 --> 02:25:36,475
You hold this boy's future
in your hands, committee.

2140
02:25:37,685 --> 02:25:41,230
It's a valuable future,
believe me.

2141
02:25:42,481 --> 02:25:45,151
Don't destroy it. Protect it.

2142
02:25:46,819 --> 02:25:48,237
Embrace it.

2143
02:25:48,988 --> 02:25:52,158
It's gonna make you proud one day,
I promise you.

2144
02:26:09,717 --> 02:26:11,677
How's that for cornball?

2145
02:26:33,199 --> 02:26:35,284
Nothing can shut them up, sir.

2146
02:26:39,789 --> 02:26:42,958
The disciplinary committee will take
this matter under advisement

2147
02:26:43,042 --> 02:26:45,211
in closed session.

2148
02:26:53,219 --> 02:26:55,429
What are they doin', Charlie?

2149
02:26:56,222 --> 02:26:59,392
I think they're going to come
to a decision now.

2150
02:27:02,728 --> 02:27:04,063
Very well.

2151
02:27:09,568 --> 02:27:12,405
Apparently, that meeting
will be unnecessary.

2152
02:27:13,239 --> 02:27:14,740
Mrs. Hunsaker.

2153
02:27:18,911 --> 02:27:24,166
The joint student-faculty disciplinary
committee needs no further sessions.

2154
02:27:24,250 --> 02:27:26,836
They have come to a decision.

2155
02:27:26,919 --> 02:27:31,465
Messrs. Havemeyer, Potter and Jameson
are placed on probation

2156
02:27:32,007 --> 02:27:34,969
for suspicion of ungentlemanly conduct.

2157
02:27:35,261 --> 02:27:38,514
It is further recommended
that Mr. George Willis, Jr.

2158
02:27:38,597 --> 02:27:41,809
receive neither recognition
nor commendation

2159
02:27:41,892 --> 02:27:43,686
for his cooperation.

2160
02:27:45,104 --> 02:27:49,775
Mr. Charles Simms is excused from
any further response to this incident.

2161
02:28:50,920 --> 02:28:52,129
Last step.

2162
02:28:52,213 --> 02:28:54,507
I can always count on you, Charlie.

2163
02:28:57,676 --> 02:28:59,178
Colonel!

2164
02:29:02,723 --> 02:29:04,558
I'm Christine Downes,
Colonel Slade.

2165
02:29:04,642 --> 02:29:06,268
I teach political science.

2166
02:29:06,352 --> 02:29:09,772
I wanted to tell you how much I appreciate
you speaking your mind.

2167
02:29:09,855 --> 02:29:11,690
Why, thank you.
Are you married?

2168
02:29:13,025 --> 02:29:14,151
I...

2169
02:29:16,695 --> 02:29:20,241
Went to an artillery school
at Fort Sill with a Mickey Downes.

2170
02:29:20,324 --> 02:29:21,992
Thought he might've snagged you.

2171
02:29:22,076 --> 02:29:24,245
No, I'm afraid not.

2172
02:29:25,913 --> 02:29:29,750
Colonel Slade was on
Lyndon Johnson's staff, Miss Downes.

2173
02:29:29,834 --> 02:29:32,128
Were you? Fascinating.

2174
02:29:32,211 --> 02:29:34,880
We should get together,
talk politics sometime.

2175
02:29:38,801 --> 02:29:40,636
Fleurs de Rocaille.

2176
02:29:42,346 --> 02:29:43,472
Yes.

2177
02:29:45,057 --> 02:29:47,184
Flowers from a brook.

2178
02:29:48,727 --> 02:29:50,187
That's right.

2179
02:29:53,983 --> 02:29:57,820
Well, Miss Downes,
I'll know where to find you.

2180
02:29:59,989 --> 02:30:01,407
Charlie.

2181
02:30:01,490 --> 02:30:02,825
Bye, Miss Downes.

2182
02:30:02,908 --> 02:30:04,160
Bye.

2183
02:30:07,413 --> 02:30:09,957
You don't have to tell me, Charlie.

2184
02:30:10,541 --> 02:30:11,667
5'7",

2185
02:30:13,252 --> 02:30:15,045
auburn hair,

2186
02:30:16,005 --> 02:30:18,507
beautiful brown eyes.

2187
02:30:37,276 --> 02:30:38,903
Yabba-dabba-doo.

2188
02:30:43,574 --> 02:30:44,742
Manny.

2189
02:30:47,453 --> 02:30:48,913
Oh, Colonel, this is too much.

2190
02:30:48,996 --> 02:30:50,456
Never mind, you earned it.

2191
02:30:50,539 --> 02:30:52,041
Next time Charlie and I

2192
02:30:52,124 --> 02:30:55,127
want to take a breather to New York,
we're gonna call you.

2193
02:30:55,211 --> 02:30:56,879
You can drive us both ways.

2194
02:30:56,962 --> 02:30:58,339
You're on, Colonel.

2195
02:30:58,422 --> 02:31:01,425
Not only will it be an honor,
I'll give you a rate.

2196
02:31:01,508 --> 02:31:04,136
I'll see your rate and raise you.

2197
02:31:04,220 --> 02:31:05,971
Stay outta harm's way, Manny.

2198
02:31:06,055 --> 02:31:07,181
Take care, Colonel.

2199
02:31:07,264 --> 02:31:08,557
You too.

2200
02:31:09,308 --> 02:31:11,810
- Ready?
- No. I'll take it from here.

2201
02:31:12,895 --> 02:31:14,230
You go on ahead.

2202
02:31:14,313 --> 02:31:16,607
Manny'll drive you to your dorm.

2203
02:31:18,025 --> 02:31:20,653
Come by before you go home
for Christmas.

2204
02:31:20,736 --> 02:31:22,905
We'll have a little cheer.

2205
02:31:22,988 --> 02:31:25,491
And if you like, stay for dinner.

2206
02:31:25,574 --> 02:31:28,535
Sometimes she cooks a pot roast.

2207
02:31:28,619 --> 02:31:30,287
It's almost edible.

2208
02:31:31,747 --> 02:31:34,291
All right, Colonel.
That'd be really...

2209
02:31:34,375 --> 02:31:35,834
Bye, Charlie.

2210
02:31:55,771 --> 02:31:59,441
Who's there?
That you, Francine?

2211
02:31:59,525 --> 02:32:00,484
Yes.

2212
02:32:00,567 --> 02:32:01,777
What are you doing?

2213
02:32:01,860 --> 02:32:03,821
Taking a ride.

2214
02:32:03,904 --> 02:32:05,572
Taking a ride?

2215
02:32:05,656 --> 02:32:07,992
What about you giving me a lift?

2216
02:32:08,075 --> 02:32:09,201
No.

2217
02:32:09,284 --> 02:32:10,411
No?

2218
02:32:10,911 --> 02:32:12,705
Come on, Francine.

2219
02:32:13,205 --> 02:32:16,208
We should make up.
Don't you think it's time we made up?

2220
02:32:16,709 --> 02:32:18,002
No.

2221
02:32:18,085 --> 02:32:19,753
- Francine?
- What?

2222
02:32:19,837 --> 02:32:25,134
Uncle Frank's had a really hard
Thanksgiving weekend.

2223
02:32:26,802 --> 02:32:29,388
What's that?
I hear a chipmunk.

2224
02:32:30,014 --> 02:32:31,890
Is it a walrus?

2225
02:32:32,182 --> 02:32:33,767
No, it's Willie.

2226
02:32:34,184 --> 02:32:36,812
Willie, why don't you help me
with my bag?

2227
02:32:36,895 --> 02:32:39,398
Come on, son.
Help me with my bag.

2228
02:32:39,690 --> 02:32:41,900
Come on. Come on.

2229
02:32:42,359 --> 02:32:45,946
You got it. Hold onto it.
You're strong. Come on.

2230
02:32:48,282 --> 02:32:49,742
Here we are.

2231
02:32:50,951 --> 02:32:53,537
Francine,
come on with me and Willie.

2232
02:32:53,746 --> 02:32:56,457
I'll let you make me
some marshmallow chocolate.

2233
02:32:56,540 --> 02:32:58,250
What do you say?

2234
02:32:58,542 --> 02:32:59,543
Good!
